def runAction(self, event):
		selectedColumn = self.props.selection.selectedColumn

		if selectedColumn == "participant_name":

			participantID = str(self.props.data[event.row].value.participant_id)

			system.perspective.openDock(id=id,params=params)

customMethods.script:
data = self.props.data
	isSummary = self.view.params.summary
		
	if isSummary == True:
		if not(data):
			return
		newColNames = ['Event Name', 'Facilitator','Date','Start Time','Duration(Hours)','Attendance', 'Description']
		newRows = []
		for i in range(data.getRowCount()):
			dateVal = data.getValueAt(i,'date')
			timeVal = data.getValueAt(i,'startsOn')
			if dateVal is not None:
				dateVal = system.date.format(dateVal, 'MM/dd/yyyy')
			if timeVal is not None:
				timeVal = system.date.format(timeVal, 'hh:mm a')
			oneRow = [data.getValueAt(i,'EventName'),data.getValueAt(i,'facilitator'),dateVal, timeVal, data.getValueAt(i,'duration_hours'),data.getValueAt(i,'attendance'),data.getValueAt(i,'description')]
			newRows.append(oneRow)
		datasetForExcel = system.dataset.toDataSet(newColNames, newRows)
		xls = system.dataset.toExcel(True, datasetForExcel)
		system.perspective.download("Attendance_History_Summary.xlsx", xls)
